The paper deals with the approximability of real-valued functions, which is a topic that falls under the scope of computational complexity (cs.CC) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of juntas, which are functions of a small number of variables, is a common technique in computational complexity and discrete mathematics (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the use of learning algorithms, which is a topic in both machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of error and approximation, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT).
